WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.468 --> 00:00:03.770
-While the White House is
engulfed in scandal and chaos,

00:00:03.770 --> 00:00:05.905
it may seem like President Trump
is getting nothing done,

00:00:05.905 --> 00:00:07.373
but that's not necessarily
the case.

00:00:07.373 --> 00:00:09.808
For example, he's already
signed an executive order

00:00:09.808 --> 00:00:11.010
on religious liberty.

00:00:11.010 --> 00:00:12.178
So we decided to take a break

00:00:12.178 --> 00:00:13.613
from the breaking news
of the day

00:00:13.613 --> 00:00:16.015
and look at Trump's evolving
views on religion, faith,

00:00:16.015 --> 00:00:17.817
and the separation
of church and state.

00:00:17.817 --> 00:00:19.585
It's time for "The Check In."

00:00:19.585 --> 00:00:23.055
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:00:23.055 --> 00:00:24.957
Now that he's president,

00:00:24.957 --> 00:00:27.093
Trump is realizing just
how difficult the job is,

00:00:27.093 --> 00:00:28.528
and he doesn't have much
to show for it.

00:00:28.528 --> 00:00:29.796
His health care bill failed,

00:00:29.796 --> 00:00:31.097
there's constant infighting

00:00:31.097 --> 00:00:32.565
and staff changes
in the White House,

00:00:32.565 --> 00:00:34.334
and of course
the Russia investigation

00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:35.968
continues to loom over him.

00:00:35.968 --> 00:00:37.637
And it's often
in dark times like this

00:00:37.637 --> 00:00:39.338
that a man will turn to God.

00:00:39.338 --> 00:00:43.175
-Take care of the people
God put into your life.

00:00:43.175 --> 00:00:47.146
We want our children to know
the blessings of God.

00:00:47.146 --> 00:00:52.718
Have a great life and love your
country and love your God, okay?

00:00:52.718 --> 00:00:56.789 line:0%
In America,
we don't worship government.

00:00:56.789 --> 00:00:59.425 line:0%
We worship God.

00:00:59.425 --> 00:01:01.093
-Oh, don't worry.

00:01:01.093 --> 00:01:02.862
Nobody is worshipping
government.

00:01:02.862 --> 00:01:04.063
[ Laughter ]

00:01:04.063 --> 00:01:06.466
I didn't take three hours
at the DMV

00:01:06.466 --> 00:01:10.169
because I had to push through
throngs of worshippers.

00:01:10.169 --> 00:01:14.073
In fact, I heard the Lord's name
taken in vain a lot.

00:01:14.073 --> 00:01:16.142
Now, admittedly, Trump did talk

00:01:16.142 --> 00:01:17.810
about God a lot
during the campaign,

00:01:17.810 --> 00:01:20.780
but what he had to say about God
was a real mixed bag.

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:23.883 line:0%
-I don't bring God into that
picture. I don't.

00:01:23.883 --> 00:01:27.854 line:0%
Why do I have to repent, why do
I have to ask for forgiveness,

00:01:27.854 --> 00:01:30.055 line:0%
if you're not making mistakes?

00:01:30.055 --> 00:01:31.591 line:0%
I say God is the ultimate.

00:01:31.591 --> 00:01:33.426
You know, you look at this --
you look at this incredible --

00:01:33.426 --> 00:01:35.061
here we are in
the Pacific Ocean.

00:01:35.061 --> 00:01:36.195
How did I ever own this?

00:01:36.195 --> 00:01:37.897
I bought it 15 years ago.

00:01:37.897 --> 00:01:40.266
I made one of the great deals
they say ever.

00:01:40.266 --> 00:01:43.769
-We love the Bible.
It's the best.

00:01:43.769 --> 00:01:46.105
We love "The Art of the Deal,"

00:01:46.105 --> 00:01:49.709
but the Bible is far, far,
far superior, right? Yes.

00:01:49.709 --> 00:01:52.445
-Not only is the Bible better
than "The Art of the Deal,"

00:01:52.445 --> 00:01:55.247
it's also the opposite.

00:01:55.247 --> 00:01:56.749
The only thing
they have in common

00:01:56.749 --> 00:01:59.419
is that Trump has never read
either of them.

00:01:59.419 --> 00:02:01.120
[ Laughter ]

00:02:01.120 --> 00:02:03.389
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:02:03.389 --> 00:02:06.126
Now, one moment
that best illustrated

00:02:06.126 --> 00:02:08.094
Trump's unfamiliarity
with the Bible

00:02:08.094 --> 00:02:10.029
was when he referred to
Second Corinthians

00:02:10.029 --> 00:02:11.731
during a speech
at Liberty University

00:02:11.731 --> 00:02:13.299
but called it something else.

00:02:13.299 --> 00:02:15.668
-i hear this is a major theme
right here,

00:02:15.668 --> 00:02:17.570
but Two Corinthians, right,

00:02:17.570 --> 00:02:21.507
Two Corinthians 3:17,
that's the whole ball game.

00:02:21.507 --> 00:02:23.543
-Two Corinthians,

00:02:23.543 --> 00:02:25.845
like it's a sequel
to an action movie.

00:02:25.845 --> 00:02:30.316
"Who can forget the famous line
from 'Two Fast Two Corinthians'

00:02:30.316 --> 00:02:32.918
when Vin Diesel said to Jesus,

00:02:32.918 --> 00:02:36.356
'Hey, long hair,
pop the clutch and let's ride.'"

00:02:36.356 --> 00:02:37.823
[ Laughter ]

00:02:37.823 --> 00:02:43.963
And then there's the question
of Trump's church attendance.

00:02:43.963 --> 00:02:45.631
Based on where
he spends his Sundays,

00:02:45.631 --> 00:02:47.400
it's likely
his most common prayer is,

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:49.802
"God, please don't let me hit it
in the water."

00:02:49.802 --> 00:02:51.938
And according to a Politico
article from April,

00:02:51.938 --> 00:02:53.572
aside from Trump attending
church services

00:02:53.572 --> 00:02:55.507
on inauguration day,
making an appearance

00:02:55.507 --> 00:02:56.676
at the National
Prayer Breakfast,

00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:57.977
and going to service
on Easter...

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:03.449
And that makes sense,
because Trump would hate church.

00:03:03.449 --> 00:03:07.086
It's an hour of people talking
about someone other than him.

00:03:07.086 --> 00:03:09.355
"Is this whole thing"--

00:03:09.355 --> 00:03:12.959
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:03:12.959 --> 00:03:15.995
"Is this whole thing
gonna be about Jesus?

00:03:15.995 --> 00:03:19.265
Did you know he had zero hotels?

00:03:19.265 --> 00:03:21.134
True story.

00:03:21.134 --> 00:03:23.936
On the day he was born, he could
not get a hotel reservation."

00:03:23.936 --> 00:03:27.440
[ Laughter ]

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:28.807
"It's sad."

00:03:28.807 --> 00:03:33.412
But still,
Trump is trying to take steps

00:03:33.412 --> 00:03:35.281
to please his evangelical base.

00:03:35.281 --> 00:03:37.115
In May,
on the National Day of Prayer,

00:03:37.115 --> 00:03:39.185
Trumped signed an executive
order on what he called

00:03:39.185 --> 00:03:41.487
the promotion of free speech
and religious liberty,

00:03:41.487 --> 00:03:44.456
which would allow churches and
other religious organizations

00:03:44.456 --> 00:03:46.225
to become more
politically active.

00:03:46.225 --> 00:03:47.994
And it provides
regulatory relief

00:03:47.994 --> 00:03:49.796
for organizations
that object to provisions

00:03:49.796 --> 00:03:51.331
in the Affordable Care Act,

00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:53.232
like including
contraception coverage

00:03:53.232 --> 00:03:54.633
in workers' health plans.

00:03:54.633 --> 00:03:57.303
In fact, during Trump's speech
about the executive order,

00:03:57.303 --> 00:03:58.971
he invited a group of nuns

00:03:58.971 --> 00:04:01.007
who refused to abide
by this original rule

00:04:01.007 --> 00:04:03.209
and had taken their case
all the way to the Supreme Court

00:04:03.209 --> 00:04:04.276
up to the podium.

00:04:04.276 --> 00:04:05.845
-Come on up here, Sister.

00:04:05.845 --> 00:04:07.714
Come on up. Right?

00:04:07.714 --> 00:04:10.183
Come on up.

00:04:10.183 --> 00:04:14.319
[ Applause ]

00:04:14.319 --> 00:04:16.055
-Pleased to meet you.

00:04:16.055 --> 00:04:17.490
-Congratulations.

00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:18.957
They sort of just won a lawsuit.

00:04:18.957 --> 00:04:20.459
That was pretty good.

00:04:20.459 --> 00:04:22.728
